criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Anterior myocardial infarct (anterior myocardial infarct is defined as persistent
             chest pain for 30 mins at least, with ST-segment elevation of at least 0.2 mV in two
             or more contiguous precordial leads) within 12 hours after onsets of symptom;

          -  Left anterior descending (LAD) as culprit vessel, with TIMI 0-1 grade.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  significant valvular disease;

          -  cardiomyopathy; l

          -  left bundle branch block;

          -  atrial fibrillation;

          -  previous myocardial infarction (MI);

          -  history of cardiac surgery;

          -  pacemaker implantation.
